As I said before, the evaluation

00:37:14.610 --> 00:37:16.130
of staff plays a special role

00:37:16.130 --> 00:37:17.550
in career planning.

00:37:17.930 --> 00:37:19.150
And here on this slide we see the

00:37:19.150 --> 00:37:21.850
main blocks of evaluation of personnel,

00:37:23.250 --> 00:37:25.630
qualities that are important

00:37:25.630 --> 00:37:27.770
to evaluate in terms of career planning.

00:37:28.070 --> 00:37:29.550
These are professional skills,

00:37:29.550 --> 00:37:31.690
management skills and motivation.

00:37:32.070 --> 00:37:33.430
To professional skills we

00:37:33.430 --> 00:37:36.570
here refer to what relates to

00:37:36.570 --> 00:37:38.850
the professional specialization

00:37:38.850 --> 00:37:41.130
of this employee.

00:37:41.650 --> 00:37:44.050
For a programmer, this can be the

00:37:44.050 --> 00:37:45.470
possession of certain

00:37:45.470 --> 00:37:48.070
programming technologies, for a lawyer,

00:37:48.070 --> 00:37:49.610
it can be his specialization

00:37:49.610 --> 00:37:51.790
within a certain legislation,

00:37:51.790 --> 00:37:54.430
for financiers, it can also

00:37:54.430 --> 00:37:56.150
be their specialization and their

00:37:56.150 --> 00:37:58.850
level of knowledge and skills

00:37:58.850 --> 00:38:00.930
in a particular professional

00:38:00.930 --> 00:38:02.310
field.

00:38:02.310 --> 00:38:04.270
For the evaluation of professional

00:38:04.270 --> 00:38:06.770
skills, expert assessment of

00:38:06.770 --> 00:38:09.170
the manager or special professional

00:38:09.530 --> 00:38:11.810
tests are most often used.

00:38:11.890 --> 00:38:13.170
And of course, it is very

00:38:13.170 --> 00:38:13.990
convenient to use professional

00:38:13.990 --> 00:38:15.930
tests, because they allow you to

00:38:15.930 --> 00:38:18.270
simultaneously evaluate a very

00:38:18.270 --> 00:38:21.110
large number of people by the

00:38:21.110 --> 00:38:24.070
standard method and store this

00:38:24.070 --> 00:38:26.230
data in digital form.

00:38:26.290 --> 00:38:28.110
For example, once a very large company

00:38:28.110 --> 00:38:31.070
wants to evaluate a large

00:38:31.070 --> 00:38:32.350
number of single-professional

00:38:32.350 --> 00:38:34.130
specialists at the same time,

00:38:34.130 --> 00:38:35.830
a professional test is usually

00:38:35.830 --> 00:38:37.770
developed with the help of,,

00:38:37.790 --> 00:38:39.230
external providers or internal

00:38:39.350 --> 00:38:40.910
specialists.

00:38:40.930 --> 00:38:42.970
And with this test, a mass evaluation

00:38:42.970 --> 00:38:46.150
of employees of these units is carried out.

00:38:46.790 --> 00:38:48.290
The second major assessment block is the

00:38:48.290 --> 00:38:49.850
assessment of management skills.

00:38:50.010 --> 00:38:52.430
Here this block is important

00:38:52.430 --> 00:38:54.030
for us precisely so that we

00:38:54.030 --> 00:38:55.910
can assess what management potential

00:38:55.910 --> 00:38:58.070
a given employee has and how much

00:38:58.070 --> 00:39:00.210
in the near or distant future

00:39:00.210 --> 00:39:02.330
we can consider this specialist

00:39:02.330 --> 00:39:04.010
to a management position but here

00:39:04.010 --> 00:39:07.070
there is such an afarism that if

00:39:07.070 --> 00:39:09.230
we promote a super professional

00:39:09.230 --> 00:39:11.130
to the level of a manager we get

00:39:11.130 --> 00:39:12.870
a bad manager and lose a professional

00:39:12.870 --> 00:39:14.450
of course this is not always

00:39:14.450 --> 00:39:16.610
so so important so to evaluate

00:39:16.610 --> 00:39:19.530
and relate the professional

00:39:19.530 --> 00:39:20.850
skills of a person,

00:39:21.310 --> 00:39:22.890
his management potential

00:39:23.130 --> 00:39:25.330
and motivation.

00:39:25.570 --> 00:39:27.950
It is worth noting that if

00:39:27.950 --> 00:39:30.590
the employee does not yet

00:39:30.590 --> 00:39:32.450
occupy a management position,

00:39:32.450 --> 00:39:34.270
then we are unlikely to have

00:39:34.490 --> 00:39:36.830
experience of evaluating it

00:39:36.830 --> 00:39:38.230
in terms of its management

00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:39.430
skills.

00:39:39.790 --> 00:39:41.670
Here, in this case, you can give

00:39:41.670 --> 00:39:43.290
the employee a temporary project,

00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:45.690
a temporary working group, so that

00:39:45.690 --> 00:39:47.910
he can try himself in this capacity,

00:39:47.910 --> 00:39:48.930
as a manager, and so

00:39:48.930 --> 00:39:51.170
that colleagues and his

00:39:51.170 --> 00:39:53.510
managers can evaluate his

00:39:53.510 --> 00:39:55.650
management skills.

00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:57.810
And to assess the managerial

00:39:57.810 --> 00:39:59.750
potential of a person, case methods,

00:40:00.310 --> 00:40:02.030
assessment centers or 360

00:40:02.310 --> 00:40:05.470
interviews are usually used.

00:40:06.310 --> 00:40:08.070
And a very important point is also

00:40:08.070 --> 00:40:10.130
the evaluation of employee

00:40:10.130 --> 00:40:12.330
motivation for his career.

00:40:12.910 --> 00:40:14.130
Each of us, of course,

00:40:14.270 --> 00:40:16.230
has faced strong professionals

00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:18.390
who don’t want to hear anything

00:40:18.390 --> 00:40:20.590
about a possible career, either

00:40:20.810 --> 00:40:22.550
horizontal or vertical.

00:40:22.790 --> 00:40:25.370
They have already reached a comfortable

00:40:25.370 --> 00:40:27.030
professional level, occupy

00:40:27.270 --> 00:40:31.130
a certain position and perform

00:40:31.130 --> 00:40:33.330
a certain range of functions

00:40:33.330 --> 00:40:36.230
and bear a certain responsibility.

00:40:36.390 --> 00:40:38.430
They are not ready to even discuss

00:40:38.430 --> 00:40:40.910
the possibilities of expanding their

00:40:40.910 --> 00:40:42.970
functionality or the possibilities

00:40:42.970 --> 00:40:45.010
of growth, as if it was not profitable

00:40:45.010 --> 00:40:46.350
for companies.

00:40:47.050 --> 00:40:49.630
This is of course a special case.

00:40:50.150 --> 00:40:51.030
And, as you and I know,

00:40:51.370 --> 00:40:52.370
certain corporate cultures,

00:40:52.370 --> 00:40:54.190
a number of companies, they

00:40:54.190 --> 00:40:56.250
despise the principle of “either

00:40:56.270 --> 00:41:00.030
up or off board” and simply physically

00:41:00.030 --> 00:41:02.130
dismiss employees who do not

00:41:02.130 --> 00:41:03.210
advance in careers.

00:41:03.570 --> 00:41:05.350
Well, or create such conditions

00:41:05.510 --> 00:41:07.310
when such employees are forced

00:41:07.310 --> 00:41:09.730
to be fired, because sitting

00:41:09.730 --> 00:41:11.210
in one place, sitting in one place,

00:41:11.210 --> 00:41:13.630
in these companies is not popular.

00:41:14.410 --> 00:41:16.370
But most companies tolerate

00:41:16.370 --> 00:41:18.430
such stars, which occupy a comfortable

00:41:18.430 --> 00:41:19.850
professional position

00:41:19.850 --> 00:41:21.270
for them.

00:41:21.530 --> 00:41:22.870
They are unique specialists

00:41:22.870 --> 00:41:24.550
and meet the needs

00:41:24.550 --> 00:41:25.770
of the company.

00:41:26.130 --> 00:41:27.550
Such employees, for example, can

00:41:27.550 --> 00:41:28.950
be programmers at any age,

00:41:28.950 --> 00:41:31.570
at maturity, when the company has

00:41:31.570 --> 00:41:33.350
repeatedly addressed them on the

00:41:33.350 --> 00:41:36.630
topic of project leadership,

00:41:36.630 --> 00:41:38.190
management of departments,

00:41:38.190 --> 00:41:40.390
but they refuse to do so and

00:41:40.390 --> 00:41:42.330
occupy a comfortable position

00:41:42.330 --> 00:41:43.690
for themselves.

00:41:43.950 --> 00:41:46.070
Companies here have to tolerate

00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:48.670
this if the interests of the

00:41:48.670 --> 00:41:50.170
company, the interests of

00:41:50.170 --> 00:41:51.730
employees coincide.

00:41:52.130 --> 00:41:54.430
But in other cases, there is a special

00:41:54.430 --> 00:41:55.990
job here.

00:41:56.050 --> 00:41:58.130
Thus, in terms of evaluation, it

00:41:58.130 --> 00:42:00.010
is very important to evaluate exactly

00:42:00.010 --> 00:42:01.370
three blocks, as professional,

00:42:01.470 --> 00:42:02.870
managerial and motivational.

00:42:02.890 --> 00:42:05.450
Motivation that can very seriously

00:42:05.450 --> 00:42:07.930
affect our understanding of career

00:42:07.930 --> 00:42:10.250
planning for this employee and here

00:42:10.250 --> 00:42:12.850
on the next slide he is so small

00:42:12.850 --> 00:42:14.010
but nevertheless here I

00:42:14.010 --> 00:42:16.510
tried to reflect the main basic

00:42:16.510 --> 00:42:18.450
issues that we can discuss

00:42:18.450 --> 00:42:21.770
with the person on a career planning

00:42:21.770 --> 00:42:24.690
interview in one of the companies

00:42:24.690 --> 00:42:26.810
I managed to implement a holistic

00:42:26.810 --> 00:42:30.250
project specifically on

00:42:30.250 --> 00:42:31.930
career planning which was

00:42:31.930 --> 00:42:33.350
initially not related to

00:42:33.350 --> 00:42:36.050
the organizational structure

00:42:36.050 --> 00:42:37.710
or the block of training

00:42:37.770 --> 00:42:39.890
and development.

00:42:40.010 --> 00:42:42.650
And so we initiated structured

00:42:42.650 --> 00:42:44.050
career planning interviews

00:42:44.050 --> 00:42:45.890
with each employee in

00:42:45.890 --> 00:42:47.090
the company.

00:42:47.570 --> 00:42:50.190
I can share with you this emotional

00:42:50.190 --> 00:42:53.790
experience.

00:42:53.890 --> 00:42:55.910
It turned out to be very significant

00:42:55.910 --> 00:42:57.810
for most employees.

00:42:58.050 --> 00:43:00.170
And they just said thank you for

00:43:00.170 --> 00:43:02.010
talking to them about their ambitions,

00:43:02.010 --> 00:43:03.730
their professional motivation,

00:43:03.730 --> 00:43:05.510
about who they would like

00:43:05.510 --> 00:43:07.530
to be in a year, two years.

00:43:08.050 --> 00:43:09.130
But I also had to touch

00:43:09.130 --> 00:43:11.310
questions about the past of

00:43:11.310 --> 00:43:13.310
employees, how they grew up in their

00:43:13.310 --> 00:43:15.170
careers, what they think is

00:43:15.170 --> 00:43:16.670
most important to themselves,

00:43:16.670 --> 00:43:18.830
what they are proud of.

00:43:19.210 --> 00:43:21.110
And it was such a full range

00:43:21.110 --> 00:43:23.410
of information that he allowed me

00:43:23.410 --> 00:43:25.910
to give recommendations to the company

00:43:26.150 --> 00:43:27.750
on what direction we could

00:43:27.750 --> 00:43:29.130
develop this employee.

00:43:29.130 --> 00:43:30.770
Well, in this slide with

00:43:30.770 --> 00:43:33.950
the blue I highlighted the main

00:43:33.950 --> 00:43:36.890
questions that I think are most

00:43:36.890 --> 00:43:40.330
informative and may not be quite

00:43:40.330 --> 00:43:44.470
banal for such communication.

00:43:45.630 --> 00:43:47.350
A career planning interview in

00:43:47.350 --> 00:43:48.970
a number of companies

00:43:48.970 --> 00:43:51.530
can be conducted with all employees

00:43:51.530 --> 00:43:53.210
of certain divisions, or

00:43:53.210 --> 00:43:54.450
all divisions.

00:43:54.450 --> 00:43:56.710
It may be linked to the performance

00:43:56.710 --> 00:43:59.210
assessment procedure.

00:43:59.730 --> 00:44:01.610
And in some companies, career planning

00:44:01.610 --> 00:44:03.010
interviews are conducted only with

00:44:03.010 --> 00:44:05.790
employees who are included in

00:44:05.790 --> 00:44:10.010
the pool or hi-po resource.

00:44:10.290 --> 00:44:11.970
These are highly potential

00:44:11.970 --> 00:44:16.070
employees, on which the company

00:44:16.070 --> 00:44:17.570
is betting in the long run and

00:44:17.570 --> 00:44:21.050
is considered the right and can be

00:44:21.050 --> 00:44:22.710
the most cost-effective, if the company

00:44:22.770 --> 00:44:23.890
can not afford to plan a career

00:44:23.890 --> 00:44:25.810
for all employees, it is considered

00:44:25.810 --> 00:44:27.750
rational to plan it at least

00:44:27.750 --> 00:44:29.410
for stars who have already manifested

00:44:29.410 --> 00:44:32.290
themselves in the results of

00:44:32.290 --> 00:44:36.870
their work, in the projects

00:44:36.870 --> 00:44:38.810
they are involved in or which

00:44:38.870 --> 00:44:40.130
they are leading.

00:44:40.350 --> 00:44:42.030
And then such interviews are

00:44:42.030 --> 00:44:43.990
conducted with such employees.

00:44:44.250 --> 00:44:46.250
But in our experience with you,

00:44:46.470 --> 00:44:48.410
of course, there were cases when

00:44:48.410 --> 00:44:51.070
such an interview it was provoked

00:44:51.070 --> 00:44:53.190
by the desire of a person to resign

00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:55.110
when a person came to the manager

00:44:55.110 --> 00:44:58.230
already practically a statement

00:44:58.230 --> 00:44:59.910
and then the manager sent

00:44:59.910 --> 00:45:01.750
this person to the HR department

00:45:01.750 --> 00:45:05.870
and asked us to offer some option

00:45:05.870 --> 00:45:07.910
to motivate an employee of a

00:45:07.910 --> 00:45:09.830
valuable employee to stay in

00:45:09.830 --> 00:45:11.810
the company and then of course

00:45:11.810 --> 00:45:13.790
all we are talking about

00:45:13.790 --> 00:45:15.130
in terms of career

00:45:15.130 --> 00:45:16.870
planning here all applicable

00:45:16.870 --> 00:45:19.390
and the process begins with

00:45:19.390 --> 00:45:21.790
a career planning interview.

00:45:22.130 --> 00:45:24.230
When we identify the interests

00:45:24.230 --> 00:45:26.490
of an employee, we talk to him

00:45:26.490 --> 00:45:30.290
as if for life, for what

00:45:30.290 --> 00:45:32.390
he likes in our company, what

00:45:32.390 --> 00:45:34.210
possible prospects.

00:45:34.290 --> 00:45:36.810
And here it is very important to expand

00:45:36.810 --> 00:45:39.110
the sphere of discussion with the employee

00:45:39.110 --> 00:45:43.130
as much as possible so that he is not

00:45:43.130 --> 00:45:45.930
stiffened by hierarchy, not stiffened

00:45:45.930 --> 00:45:48.310
by the organizational structure.

00:45:48.310 --> 00:45:50.070
In order to be able to openly discuss

00:45:50.070 --> 00:45:51.750
with him in what directions

00:45:51.750 --> 00:45:54.050
he sees himself, in what positions

00:45:54.050 --> 00:45:55.470
and in what directions he

00:45:55.470 --> 00:45:57.030
would be interested in continuing

00:45:57.030 --> 00:45:57.990
his career.

00:45:58.590 --> 00:45:59.830
And as a result of such

00:45:59.830 --> 00:46:01.250
career planning, it can be very

00:46:01.250 --> 00:46:03.110
non-trivial organizational

00:46:03.110 --> 00:46:05.310
decisions, when a person from

00:46:05.310 --> 00:46:06.690
one functional direction moves

00:46:06.690 --> 00:46:09.050
to adjacent or completely

00:46:09.050 --> 00:46:10.690
into another direction.

00:46:11.090 --> 00:46:14.290
But we will talk about this further.

